	   <tr><td colspan=2>I played last night, in 12 hours the ghoul arch magus popped 5 times and dropped the robe 4 of them. My group was so nice and let me have it for my epic after a reroll in which the first time I did not win.<br><br>But either we got really lucky or this is common. The magus' PH is in the corner by the bookshelf and hidden wall. He is 45 and if you are camping in the room you can catch him without a pet. He nukes for not a whole lot, but need to have a cleric or 2 sub par healers. He has a lot of HP, around 3k or so. The froggie village was empty that day so our group pulled the hand and lord also. Everything down there except maybe the hand is on a 28 minute spawn, so have someone keep track. You can easily get a lot of loot and exp with a smart and well rounded group and a good puller. We only had one death and that was at the start when the cleric got killed from those new healing hate changes, but otherwise we were fine.<br><br>Lord is a nasty git, maybe around 7k hp and a harm touch to boot. he dropped the SSB both times we got him so I can't give any advice on how hard he is with a yak, but I would guess a lot harder.<br><br>Good luck.<br>&nbsp;<br>Pratell Kurokage<br>Damn straight.</td></tr>
